commit.message: updated dist.ini to automate some things. moved some tests into the xt directory. hang onto makefile, meta, and README.md
common git and repo files to help keep things clean
ignore the sendmail.log generated during testing

Fudge the send() command so that it'll play ball with Net::SMTP::TLS

The differences with the plain SMTP stuff are:

* ::TLS doesn't use username/password, but rather User/Password.

* The auth is done in the new(), not in a distinct function

* mail() doesn't return anything, so fail on the eval{ }

* data is not sent with a simple data(), but requires a more compex invocation
